nodes.text: Coruscant Security Force Divisional Headquarters  (Quadrant A-89)

A Coruscant Security Force Divisional Headquarters served as the base of operations for the Coruscant Security Force police division assigned to Quadrant A-89 of Galactic City on the planet Coruscant. The divisional headquarters was a building complex that housed various offices for police officers. The CSF's Forensics Unit also operated a morgue located inside the building.

In 21 BBY, CSF Captain Jaller Obrim requested that Sergeant Kal Skirata of the Grand Army of the Republic come to the morgue to identify the body of Paxaz Izhiq, a Falleen member of the Black Sun crime syndicate. Izhiq was suspected of being involved with terrorist cells on Coruscant that Skirata and his clone commandos were hunting.
The Coruscant Security Force Divisional Headquarters appeared in Republic Commando: Triple Zero, a novel written by Karen Traviss and published on February 28, 2006.
